comments: Curry (GSW) holds a bracing arm to Reaves' (LAL) side during the drive and the contact is marginal.
Green (GSW) legally contests Davis' (LAL) jump shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) brings his hand toward the ball and grazes DiVincenzo's (GSW) arm.
Brown Jr. (LAL) aligns his body along DiVincenzo's (GSW) path and marginal contact occurs at the start of the drive.
Thompson (GSW) and Reaves (LAL) engage and disengage with one another during the screen.
Iguodala (GSW) engages and disengages with Davis (LAL) as he attempts to roll toward the basket.
Davis (LAL) holds his arms out slightly as he establishes himself in a screening position in Iguodala's (GSW) path and marginal contact occurs.
Davis (LAL) and Iguodala (GSW) engage and disengage in the post.
DiVincenzo (GSW) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Iguodala (GSW) does not have his arm in a legal position when Davis (LAL) raises his arms up and arm contact occurs that causes him to lose control of the ball.
Green (GSW) turns his body slightly as he firms up in Schroder's (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
Schroder (LAL) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
Vanderbilt (LAL) and Iguodala (GSW) engage and disengage during the rebounding opportunity.
Brown Jr. (LAL) steps toward Iguodala's (GSW) space and marginal contact occurs as he slips away from the defender.
DiVincenzo (GSW) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Davis (LAL) slides his arm off of Green's (GSW) arm as he establishes  position in the post.
Green (GSW) brings his arm toward Davis' (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs at the start of Davis' drive.
Green (GSW) retreats his arm to a vertical position and grazes Davis' (LAL) arm while contesting the driving shot attempt.
DiVincenzo (GSW) establishes himself in Brown Jr.'s (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the screen.
Curry (GSW) firms up on his left leg and marginal contact occurs with Brown Jr. (LAL) as he goes under the screen.
Brown Jr. (LAL) legally contests Thompson's (GSW) perimeter shot attempt.
Vanderbilt (LAL) and DiVincenzo (GSW) simultaneously bring their hands to the rebound. The ball is deflected and the subsequent arm contact is considered incidental.
DiVincenzo (GSW) moves alongside Reaves' (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs.
Poole (GSW) makes foot to foot contact with Schroder's (LAL) side and affects Schroder's SQBR..
Green (GSW) backs up slightly and marginal contact occurs with Reaves (LAL), who is defending the dribbler.
Vanderbilt (LAL) legally contests DiVincenzo's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
The ball last touches Davis' (LAL) foot before going out of bounds and possession is properly retained by Golden State.
Green (GSW) establishes himself in Schroder's (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
Schroder (LAL) legally contests Curry's (GSW) perimeter shot attempt.
Brown Jr. (LAL) grabs and pulls DiVincenzo's (GSW) arm as he gathers the ball, affecting his SQBR.
Curry (GSW) and Brown Jr. (LAL) engage and disengage during the inbound.
DiVincenzo (GSW) and Schroder (LAL) engage and disengage during the inbound.
Curry (GSW) commits a take foul on Reaves (LAL).
Schroder (LAL) rests his hand on Curry's (GSW) side and Schroder retracts the marginal contact as Curry retrieves the pass.
Thompson (GSW) and Reaves (LAL) engage and disengage during the inbound.
DiVincenzo (GSW) commits a take foul on Beasley (LAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of the fourth quarter or overtime.
Davis (LAL) legally contests Curry's (GSW) perimeter shot attempt.
